column5: Will be going into Wine lake saturday June 10. Does Dutchie sell fishing license . bait, bottled water Also what time do they open on sunday and can they sell beer then.
I'm pretty sure Dutchies is not a liquor store.

I have purchased crawlers and leeches at Dutchies in the past, and I believe, but am not certain, that licenses are also available. I have also purchased beer at Dutchies on Sunday afternoon. Can't help you with their opening time though.

[font color=green size=3][b]licences - yes, bait- they quit carrying minnows a few years back,may have crawlers, 8:00am open, beer- they are a LCBO store, water- I don't recall seeing anything but gallons jugs. Wish'in I was fish'in on Wabby
thks Trailer , been going to Wine a long time , you seem to know area pretty well , whats deal with wabby reservation . Just curious

[font color=green size=3][b]I guess I've not payed much attention to their landing at the reservation. We're usually out in the middle in travling mode as we go by. I have heard that someone has set up a small sawmill on the reserve and is producing excellent lumber building materials at a resonable price. Wish'in I was fish'in on Wabby
